<br>
I play a R6L2 Mercenary on Palomides, and he is my main character.  I occasionally play a Healer on Galahad to get away from the overpopulation issues that exists on Palomides, but I'm already digressing.<br>
<br>
First off, I'm not a regular on Pendragon.  I have, and do test various specs and RA's to influence my choices on Palomides.  I log on new characters to check out particular features in testing that can/would affect my character.  Other than that, most of my knowledge of the class comes from playing on Palomides, or from digging in various forums and asking questions that I'm sure some of you have thought were &quot;noobish&quot;.<br>
<br>
My point?  Well, I don't intend to do all the testing.  I'd much rather be a focus for the information that Mercenaries I've come to know and trust (as far as their character on forums as well as their correct knowledge) such as Nirala, Fingoniel, Kate, Uhno, etc..  I'll only break out my characters on Pendragon to test issues that gain importance, either from my &quot;inside information&quot; or from community feedback, assuming what I'm presented with isn't conclusive enough.  Another thing, I haven't leveled up a Mercenary since the game was released.  Already, things weren't as they were.  Any issues with low level Mercenaries and PvE will have to come from the community.  I occasionally do big PvE raids like Sidi and the Dragon, but don't feel that's relevant to the Mercenary class.<br>
<br>
In RL I'm an engineering graduate and I work in a related field (CAD).  I like numbers, I like parsing.  I like to figure out what the numbers mean, and I collect my own logs from live servers regularly.  Although my statistics class was many many years ago, I understand the fundamentals.  What I'm getting at, is I'm more focused on numbers than opinions.<br>
<br>
My views on the Mercenary Class.  I personally think Mercenaries are close to being a complete class as far as end game RvR is concerned.  Most of the issues are superfluous to our function and would be nice to have fixed, but IMO shouldn't take precedence over other classes that need the attention first.<br>
<br>
I won't go into detail right now, as I haven't had a chance to organize my thoughts, but as far as Styles and RA's, there's supposedly reviews that will look at those.  Kate has already brought attention to what needs attention, and at most I think I will just follow her lead until these reviews have come and pass.  The other issues, are shield swapping for those that choose that spec path, the Charge ability, and Dirty Tricks.  <br>
<br>
Dirty Tricks in its current implementation is much better than it was.  I do use it now in RvR to try and save my support classes that are being attacked by melee.  However, I feel one further tweak should be added that has &quot;some&quot; effect on those classes that never &quot;melee&quot;.  I do not know what this &quot;tweak&quot; should be.  I just view Dirty Tricks as not quite complete.<br>
<br>
I hope this gives some idea to the community on my views and my stances.  What I want to be is a focus point for information regarding Mercenaries, not a one man army.<br>
<br>
